Well personally I like to use single or 2 line dithering, followed by larger area of constant colour. It's &quot;best of both&quot;, you get the solidity of constant colours, but the smoothness of dithering in the transitions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Jan 19, 2014 3:24 pm</p><hr />
